    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "While i would tend to agree this is more a brownie bug than an OpenZeppelin bug, the practice is discouraged on one hand, and also the philosophy behind the library is to accommodate as much as possible (e.g. what SafeERC20 is doing, fixing broken ERC20 tokens transfers). Besides, previous versions did not use that syntax, so it's kind of a breaking change (it was compiling with previous versions, and no longer is).\r\n\r\nAnyhow, thanks for this wonderful library and have a great day!",
